[SPEAKER_03] is the question about sequencing.

1193
01:37:18,640 --> 01:37:21,279
[SPEAKER_03] The whole approach as we have heard this morning

1194
01:37:21,279 --> 01:37:25,960
[SPEAKER_03] comes really from the very broad area.

1195
01:37:25,960 --> 01:37:27,380
[SPEAKER_03] We want to deepen EMU.

1196
01:37:27,380 --> 01:37:29,739
[SPEAKER_03] We want to make EMU more competitive.

1197
01:37:29,739 --> 01:37:31,460
[SPEAKER_03] if we want to make it more stable

1198
01:37:31,460 --> 01:37:34,680
[SPEAKER_03] to enforce growth potential.

1199
01:37:34,680 --> 01:37:38,439
[SPEAKER_03] Then you go to the financial market aspect

1200
01:37:38,439 --> 01:37:42,199
[SPEAKER_03] and then we say we want to make financial markets more stable.

1201
01:37:42,199 --> 01:37:44,560
[SPEAKER_03] We're pushing for capital markets union

1202
01:37:44,560 --> 01:37:46,619
[SPEAKER_03] to push these issues.

1203
01:37:47,300 --> 01:37:50,180
[SPEAKER_03] We are sorry to say that we are not

1204
01:37:50,180 --> 01:37:56,659
[SPEAKER_03] or we are promoting EMU

1205
01:37:56,659 --> 01:37:58,520
[SPEAKER_03] where the banking sector does not play

1206
