1217
01:38:34,340 --> 01:38:35,840
[SPEAKER_03] and much has been done.

1218
01:38:35,840 --> 01:38:38,619
[SPEAKER_03] We are moving towards risk reduction

1219
01:38:38,619 --> 01:38:40,760
[SPEAKER_03] as we have discussed before

1220
01:38:40,760 --> 01:38:45,439
[SPEAKER_03] talking about the risk weighting of sovereign exposure.

1221
01:38:45,439 --> 01:38:47,319
[SPEAKER_03] And then only at the very end

1222
01:38:47,319 --> 01:38:49,640
[SPEAKER_03] of this very wide and long process

1223
01:38:49,640 --> 01:38:53,899
[SPEAKER_03] we talk about this common backstop issue.

1224
01:38:53,899 --> 01:38:56,699
[SPEAKER_03] In the end, I think we are,

1225
01:38:56,699 --> 01:39:02,539
[SPEAKER_03] we agree that it's difficult to imagine

1226
